template_id: openagreements-restrictive-covenant-georgia
name: OpenAgreements Employee Restrictive Covenant (Georgia)
category: non-compete
description: >-
  Georgia-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement built for the Georgia
  Restrictive Covenants Act (O.C.G.A. § 13-8-50 et seq.): confidentiality and
  trade-secret protection keyed to continued protection under § 13-8-53(e), a
  customer non-solicitation anchored to material-contact customers under
  § 13-8-53(b) with no express geographic term required, an optional non-compete
  gated on the § 13-8-53(a) covered-employee functions and drafted to reasonable
  time, geographic area, and scope within the § 13-8-57(b) two-year presumption
  window, discretionary narrowing-only judicial modification under § 13-8-53(d),
  and Georgia choice-of-law language reflecting that Georgia law is the
  touchstone for enforceability. Drafted as a starting point for licensed counsel
  review.
source_url: >-
  https://github.com/open-agreements/open-agreements/tree/main/templates/openagreements-restrictive-covenant-georgia
